label: uncl3227
comment: Code identifying the function of a location.

values.label: Place of terms of delivery
values.comment: (3018) Point or port of departure, shipment or destination, as required under the applicable terms of delivery, e.g. Incoterms.

values.label: Payment location
values.comment: [3109] To identify the place where the payment has been or should be made.

values.label: Tare check place
values.comment: Place where equipment tare has been or must be checked for official assessment.

values.label: Goods receipt place
values.comment: [3160] Place at which the goods have been received.

values.label: Place of departure
values.comment: (3214) Port, airport or other location from which a means of transport or transport equipment is scheduled to depart or has departed.

values.label: Ward bed
values.comment: A bed in a ward.

values.label: Place of delivery
values.comment: (3246) Place to which the goods are to be finally delivered under transport contract terms (operational term).

values.label: Place of destination
values.comment: (3258) Port, airport or other location to which a means of transport or transport equipment is destined.

values.label: Place of loading
values.comment: [3334] Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place at which the goods (cargo) are loaded on to the means of transport being used for their carriage.

values.label: Place of acceptance
values.comment: [3348] Place where the goods are taken over by the carrier.

values.label: Place of discharge
values.comment: [3392] Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place at which goods are unloaded from the means of transport having been used for their carriage.

values.label: Port of discharge
values.comment: Port at which the goods are discharged from the vessel used for their transport.

values.label: Place of transhipment
values.comment: [3424] Place where goods are to be or have been transferred from one means of transport to another during the course of one transport operation.

values.label: Goods item storage location
values.comment: [3385] To identify the place where a goods item is located.

values.label: Place of transfer responsibility
values.comment: Place where the responsibility is transferred.

values.label: Place of transfer of ownership
values.comment: Place where the ownership of the goods is transferred.

values.label: Border crossing place
values.comment: Place where goods are transported across a country border.

values.label: Warehouse
values.comment: [3156] Warehouse where a particular consignment is to be or has been stored.

values.label: Factory/plant
values.comment: Factory/plant relevant for a particular consignment.

values.label: Place of ultimate destination of goods
values.comment: Place where goods will ultimately be delivered.

values.label: Terms of sale place
values.comment: Place of departure, shipment or destination as specified in the terms of sale agreed between the parties.

values.label: Customs clearance location
values.comment: [3080] Place at which Customs clearance should or has taken place.

values.label: Port of release
values.comment: Port where goods are released from Customs custody.

values.label: Port of entry
values.comment: Port where final documentation is filed for Customs Entry processing.

values.label: Country
values.comment: Country relevant for a particular transaction.

values.label: City
values.comment: City or town relevant for a particular transaction or consignment.

values.label: Country of origin
values.comment: [3239] To identify the country in which the goods have been produced or manufactured, according to criteria laid down for the application of the Customs tariff or quantitative restrictions, or any measure related to trade.

values.label: Country of destination of goods
values.comment: Country to which the goods are to be delivered.

values.label: Railway station
values.comment: Name or identification of a railway station/yard relevant to a particular consignment.

values.label: Country of source
values.comment: Country in which raw material or components were originally produced prior to manufacture or assembly in another country.

values.label: Building
values.comment: A building or part thereof relevant to a particular consignment or transaction.

values.label: Beginning of chargeable section
values.comment: First rail station in a predefined section of the chargeable voyage. A complete voyage may be divided in sections, even within one country, that are separately chargeable using different tariff rules (split tariffs).

values.label: Baseport of discharge
values.comment: [3356] Place at which the cargo is discharged or unloaded from a means of transport according to the transport contract. The goods may or may not be discharged from the main means of transport at this place or port.

values.label: Baseport of loading
values.comment: [3322] Place at which the cargo is loaded on a means of transport according to the transport contract. The goods may or may not be loaded on the main means of transport at this place or port.

values.label: Exportation country
values.comment: [3220] Country from which the goods were initially exported to the importing country without any commercial transaction taking place in intermediate countries. Synonym: Country whence consigned. Country of despatch: Country from which goods are despatched between countries of a Customs union.

values.label: Country of ultimate destination
values.comment: (3216) Country known to the consignor or his agent at the time of despatch to be the final country to which the goods are to be delivered.

values.label: Consignment final exportation country
values.comment: [3331] To identify the country from which goods have been or will be consigned prior to final importation.

values.label: Consignment first destination country
values.comment: [3219] To identify the country where a consignment is off-loaded from the means of transport used for the original exportation.

values.label: Country of production
values.comment: Country where item has been or will be produced.

values.label: Country of trading
values.comment: Country where item has been or will be traded.

values.label: Consignment entry customs office location
values.comment: [3089] To identify the customs office at which the goods enter the customs territory of destination.

values.label: Consignment exit customs office location
values.comment: [3097] To identify the customs office at which the goods leave or are intended to leave the customs territory of despatch.

values.label: Place of Customs examination
values.comment: Place where Customs undertakes a physical inspection of goods to satisfy themselves that the goods' nature, origin, condition, quantity and value are in accordance with the particulars furnished on the goods declaration (CCC).

values.label: Place of authentication of document
values.comment: (3410) Place where document is signed or otherwise authenticated. Synonym: Place of issue of document.

values.label: Customs office of destination (transit)
values.comment: (3086) Customs office at which a transit operation is terminated. Synonym: Customs office of transit termination.

values.label: Region of despatch
values.comment: Region from which goods are despatched between countries of a Customs union.

values.label: Region of destination
values.comment: Region known to the consignor or his agent at the time of despatch to be the final region to which the goods are to be delivered.

values.label: Region of production
values.comment: Region where item has been or will be produced.

values.label: Transit country
values.comment: [3263] Country through which a goods or passengers are routed between the country of original departure and final destination.

values.label: Transit customs office location
values.comment: [3107] To identify the customs office which is responsible for transit formalities en-route.

values.label: Country of invalid transit guarantee
values.comment: Country in which the security or guarantee for the movement of goods under a transit procedure is not valid.

values.label: Country of destination (transit)
values.comment: Country at which a Customs transit operation is terminated. Synonym: Country of transit termination.

values.label: Charge and freight due from
values.comment: Place or point from which charges and freight are charged.

values.label: Manufacturing department
values.comment: A department within the manufacturing area (e.g. lacquering, assembly).

values.label: Freight charge payable to location
values.comment: [3102] Name of a place to which a transport charges tariff applies or where freight and other related charges are to be or have been incurred.

values.label: End of chargeable section
values.comment: Last rail station in a predefined section of the chargeable voyage. A complete voyage may be divided in sections, even within one country, that are separately chargeable using different tariff rules (split tariffs).

values.label: Place of payment
values.comment: Name of the location at which freight and charges for main transport are payable.

values.label: Full track loading or unloading
values.comment: Identification of the station proceeding to the loading or unloading of a rail wagon on a full track site. (Used only when a rail station is obliged to transfer the load on another wagon for technical reasons - e.g. damage).

values.label: Place of loss
values.comment: To identify the location where the loss occurred.

values.label: Place of arrival
values.comment: Place at which the transport means arrives.

values.label: Next port of call
values.comment: (3095) Next port which the vessel is going to call upon.

values.label: On-carriage port
values.comment: Port of discharge at which the cargo is discharged from the vessel, used for transport after the main transport (transit port).

values.label: Sub-project location
values.comment: A place at which works occur referring to a sub-project.

values.label: First optional place of discharge
values.comment: The first optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

values.label: Final port or place of discharge
values.comment: Name of the seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place at which the goods (cargo) are finally (to be) unloaded from the means of transport used for their carriage according to the transport contract.

values.label: Express railway station
values.comment: Railway station offering express transportation services.

values.label: Mixed cargo railway station
values.comment: Railway station offering mixed cargo transportation services .

values.label: Second optional place of discharge
values.comment: The second optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of shipper.

values.label: Next non-discharge port of call
values.comment: A code to identify the next port of call for a vessel where no cargo will be discharged.

values.label: Third optional place of discharge
values.comment: The third optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

values.label: Reconsolidation point
values.comment: A place where cargo is reconsolidated.

values.label: Fourth optional place of discharge
values.comment: The fourth optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

values.label: Bill of lading release office
values.comment: A location where bills of lading are released to customers.

values.label: Transhipment excluding this place
values.comment: Place/location where a transhipment from a means of transport to another means of transport is not authorised.

values.label: Transhipment limited to this place
values.comment: Only place/location where a transhipment from a means of transport to another means of transport is authorised.

values.label: Original port of loading
values.comment: (3099) The port where the goods were first loaded on a vessel.

values.label: First port of call - non-discharging
values.comment: Port in the country of destination where the conveyance initially arrives from the 'last place/port of call of conveyance' and where a conveyance will not be discharging cargoes.

values.label: First port of call - discharging
values.comment: Port in the country of destination where the conveyance initially arrives from the 'last place/port of call of conveyance' and where a conveyance will be discharging cargoes.

values.label: Place/port of first entry
values.comment: Place or port where final documentation is filed for Customs entry processing.

values.label: Place of despatch
values.comment: Place at which the goods are taken over for carriage (operational term), if different from the transport contract place of acceptance (see: 10). Synonym: Place of origin of carriage.

values.label: Fifth optional place of discharge
values.comment: The fifth optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

values.label: Pre-carriage port
values.comment: Port of loading at which the cargo is loaded on the pre- carriage vessel used for the transport prior to the main transport.

values.label: Place of delivery (by on carriage)
values.comment: [3358] Place to which the goods are to be finally delivered.

values.label: Transport contract place of acceptance
values.comment: Place at which the goods are taken over by the carrier according to the contract of carriage.

values.label: Transport contract place of destination
values.comment: Place to which the goods are destined.

values.label: Country of valid transit guarantee
values.comment: Country in which the security or guarantee for the movement of goods under a transit procedure is valid.

values.label: Place/port of conveyance initial arrival
values.comment: Place/port in the country of destination where the conveyance initially arrives from the "Last place/port of call of conveyance" (125).

values.label: Place of receipt
values.comment: Identification of the location at which the cargo is actually received.

values.label: Place of registration
values.comment: (3105) Place where the registration occurs.

values.label: Special treatment place
values.comment: Place where one or more special treatments have happened or must happen.

values.label: Place of document issue
values.comment: The place or location where a document is issued.

values.label: Routing
values.comment: Indication of a routing place.

values.label: Station of application of additional costs
values.comment: Rail station where, according to the transport contract, some chargeable operations must happen (re-weighting, re-fixing of the load, control on equipment and on consignment, etc.).

values.label: Previous port of call
values.comment: Previous port which the vessel has called upon.

values.label: Sailing destination area
values.comment: Geographical area to which the vessel's trip is destined.

values.label: Place of lodgement of documents
values.comment: Customs station where, required documents for Customs declarations, have been lodged.

values.label: Optional place of discharge
values.comment: The optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the bill of lading where cargo is discharged at the option of the shipper.

values.label: Place of empty equipment despatch
values.comment: The location from which empty equipment is despatched.

values.label: Place of empty equipment return
values.comment: The location to which empty equipment is returned.

values.label: Place/port of warehouse entry
values.comment: Location (e.g. district) within a Customs territory where a warehouse entry was filed to enter merchandise into a Customs bonded warehouse.

values.label: Country of first sale
values.comment: Name of country where firstly a sale took place.

values.label: Place of transfer
values.comment: Place at which goods are transferred from one carrier to another (contractual term).

values.label: Place of deconsolidation
values.comment: Place where a large consignment is de-grouped into smaller consignments.

values.label: Place of consumption
values.comment: Place/location where goods enter the marketplace (commerce) of the importing country.

values.label: Region of origin
values.comment: Region in which the goods have been produced or manufactured according to the criteria laid down for the purposes of the application of the Customs tariff, of quantitative restrictions or of any other measures related to trade (see: 3238).

values.label: Place of consolidation
values.comment: Place where smaller consignments of goods are grouped together into a large consignment to be transported as a larger unit.

values.label: Rate combination point
values.comment: [3369] Point over which sector rates are combined.

values.label: Place of prolongation decision of delivery delay
values.comment: Place where it has been decided to prolong the delivery delay.

values.label: Recharging place/location
values.comment: Place/location where a consignment has been changed of destination and is subject to a recharge note. (Complementary orders to modify the routing of the transport may be given, upon which a new charge calculation may be applied by the carrier).

values.label: Customs office of despatch
values.comment: Customs office from which goods are despatched between countries of a Customs union.

values.label: Region of equipment availability
values.comment: Region in which a piece of equipment is requested to be made available for on-hire.

values.label: Country of despatch
values.comment: Country from which goods are despatched within a Customs union.

values.label: Customs office of export
values.comment: Customs office from which goods are taken out of the Customs territory (CCC).

values.label: Free zone of export
values.comment: Foreign free zone (desc: see 1131 = 131) from which goods are exported to the country of importation.

values.label: Region of export/despatch
values.comment: Region from which the goods were initially exported to the importing country without any commercial transaction taking place in intermediate countries. Region of despatch: region from which goods are despatched between countries of a Customs union.

values.label: Place of collection
values.comment: Place where goods are to be or could be picked up (collected).

values.label: Customs office of departure
values.comment: Customs office at which a Customs transit operation commences (CCC).

values.label: Transit guarantee customs office location
values.comment: [3111] To identify the Customs office at which a security or guarantee for the movement of goods under a transit procedure is lodged.

values.label: Country of transhipment
values.comment: Country where goods are transferred under Customs control from the importing means of transport to the exporting means of transport within the area of one Customs office which is the office of both importation and exportation (CCC).

values.label: Customs office of destination
values.comment: Customs office where the goods are to be cleared (CCC).

values.label: Wagon-load railway station
values.comment: A railway station where rail wagons are loaded.

values.label: Siding
values.comment: A short railway track for loading or unloading rail wagons, or bypassing of trains, connected with a main track by switch.

values.label: Last place/port of call of conveyance
values.comment: Conveyance departed from this last foreign place/port of call to go to "Place/port of conveyance initial arrival" (87).

values.label: Country of previous Customs procedure
values.comment: Country in which the Customs declaration for the previous Customs procedure has been lodged.

values.label: Customs office of registration of previous Customs declaration
values.comment: Customs office where the previous Customs declaration has been lodged.

values.label: Participant sender location
values.comment: Place where a participant in the movement of goods is located and can be contacted.

values.label: Wage negotiation district
values.comment: The district to which workers belong for the purposes of union wage negotiation.

values.label: Place of ultimate destination of conveyance
values.comment: Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place to which a means of transport is ultimately destined.

values.label: Place of loading of empty equipment
values.comment: Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place where empty equipment (e.g. containers) was loaded onto means of transport.

values.label: Place of discharge of empty equipment
values.comment: Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place where empty equipment (e.g. containers) was unloaded from means of transport.

values.label: Region of delivery
values.comment: (3246) Region to which the goods are to be finally delivered under transport contract terms (operational term).

values.label: Petroleum warehouse
values.comment: Bonded petroleum warehouse or the supplier source.

values.label: Place of entry (Customs)
values.comment: Place at which the goods enter the Customs territory.

values.label: Living animals care place
values.comment: Place where living animal cares are provided.

values.label: Re-icing place
values.comment: Place where re-icing must be executed.

values.label: Weighting place
values.comment: Place where weight can be ascertained.

values.label: Marshalling yard
values.comment: Station where the wagons are disconnected and reconnected to form a new train.

values.label: Stopping station
values.comment: Station where the train must stop or is stopped for unexpected handling.

values.label: Loading dock
values.comment: Platform specially equipped for loading and unloading of rail wagons.

values.label: Port connection
values.comment: Track connecting a rail station to a dock.

values.label: Place of expiry
values.comment: [3212] Place where the documentary credit expires for presentation of required documents.

values.label: Place of negotiation
values.comment: Place where the documentary credit is to be presented for negotiation.

values.label: Claims payable place
values.comment: Place where insurance claims are payable.

values.label: Documentary credit available in
values.comment: Place where the documentary credit is available with any bank.

values.label: Transport means stowage location
values.comment: [8043] To identify a location on board a means of transport where specified goods or transport equipment has been or are to be stowed.

values.label: For transportation to
values.comment: Place/country where goods are to be transported to.

values.label: Loading on board/despatch/taking in charge at/from
values.comment: Place/country where goods have to be loaded on board, despatched or taken in charge.

values.label: Container stack position
values.comment: Stack position of a container at a terminal, depot or freight station.

values.label: Private box
values.comment: A private box used for pick-up and delivery of packages, e.g. of express packages.

values.label: Next port of discharge
values.comment: Next port at which goods are discharged from the vessel used for their transport.

values.label: Port of call
values.comment: Port where a vessel has called upon or will call upon.

values.label: Place/location of on-hire
values.comment: Place/location where an object is contracted for use.

values.label: Place/location of off-hire
values.comment: Place/location where an object's contract for use ends.

values.label: Other carriers terminal
values.comment: A carrier terminal belonging to a carrier other than the original carrier.

values.label: Country of Value Added Tax (VAT) jurisdiction
values.comment: The country governing the VAT regulation to which the transaction is subject.

values.label: Contact location
values.comment: The site where a contact is located.

values.label: Additional internal destination
values.comment: Any location within the consignee's premises where the goods are moved to.

values.label: Foreign port of call
values.comment: A code to identify the foreign port where the vessel calls at or will call at.

values.label: Maintenance location
values.comment: A location where maintenance has been or will be performed.

values.label: Place or location of sale
values.comment: Place or location at which the sale takes place.

values.label: Direct investment country
values.comment: Country in which a direct investment is made or withdrawn.

values.label: Berth
values.comment: [3416] Location in port where the vessel is berthed or moored.

values.label: Construction country
values.comment: Country in which the construction work is made.

values.label: Donation acting country
values.comment: Country acting in the donation of aid.

values.label: Payment transaction country
values.comment: Country of the foreign counterpart of the payment transaction.

values.label: Physical place of return of item
values.comment: Physical place at which the item is returned, i.e. the location where the supplier receives the item form the customer.

values.label: Relay port
values.comment: A location where cargo is transferred from one means of transport to another means of transport owned or operated by the same carrier under the same bill of lading.

values.label: Final port of discharge
values.comment: Last port at which cargo is unloaded from a vessel before the cargo is moved to a place of delivery or destination.

values.label: Place of destination for pre-stacking prior to stowage
values.comment: The destination location for which items are to be pre- stacked prior to being stowed together on a means of transport.

values.label: Reporting location
values.comment: The location to which the information being reported is applicable.

values.label: Transport contract place of despatch
values.comment: A place from which goods are despatched as per transport contract.

values.label: Place of residence
values.comment: A place where a party lives.

values.label: Activity location
values.comment: A place at which the activity occurs.

values.label: Pick-up location
values.comment: Location for pick up.

values.label: Construction site
values.comment: A place at which construction works occur.

values.label: Place of embarkation
values.comment: (3488) Place where the object is put, or goes, on board the conveyance.

values.label: Place of disembarkation
values.comment: (3490) Place where the object or person disembarks from the conveyance.

values.label: Person birth location
values.comment: [3486] Name of the place where a person was born.

values.label: Registered office
values.comment: Identifies the place or location of a registered office.

values.label: Place of incorporation
values.comment: Identifies the location of incorporation.

values.label: Place of business
values.comment: Identifies the place or location of a business.

values.label: Physical location
values.comment: Identifies the physical location.

values.label: Location to send mail
values.comment: Identifies the location to which mail is sent.

values.label: Foreign registration location
values.comment: Identifies the place or location of foreign registration.

values.label: Tax filed from location
values.comment: Identifies the location from which taxes are filed.

values.label: Filing location
values.comment: Identifies the location of the filing entity.

values.label: Former location
values.comment: Identifies an earlier or previous place or location.

values.label: Head office
values.comment: Identifies the place or location of a head office.

values.label: Property
values.comment: Identifies the place or location of property.

values.label: Correct location
values.comment: Identifies the correct place or location.

values.label: Branch location
values.comment: Identifies the place or location of a branch.

values.label: Former registered location
values.comment: Identifies the former registered location of an entity.

values.label: Future location
values.comment: Location to be used in the future.

values.label: Changed to location
values.comment: Identifies the change to location.

values.label: Place of inquiry
values.comment: Place to which an inquiry is made.

values.label: Original location
values.comment: Identifies the original location.

values.label: Country of last source
values.comment: The country where a product or service was last sourced.

values.label: Place of handling
values.comment: Place where a handling operation is to be, or has been, performed.

values.label: Country of origin as defined by transportation agency
values.comment: Country of origin as defined by the transportation agency.

values.label: Terminal
values.comment: A terminus for transport vehicles.

values.label: Sample location
values.comment: Code identifying the location from which a sample is taken.

values.label: Hospital Advanced Dependency Unit (ADU)
values.comment: A designated unit in a hospital for advanced dependency nursing care.

values.label: Hospital Neonatal Intensive Care Unit (NICU)
values.comment: A designated unit in a hospital for the provision of intensive care to neonates.

values.label: Hospital Paediatric Care Unit (PCU)
values.comment: A designated unit in a hospital for the provision of care to paediatric patients.

values.label: Hospital Intensive Care Unit (ICU)
values.comment: An intensive care unit in a hospital.

values.label: Hospital luxury room
values.comment: A room in a hospital for patient accommodation of superior standard.

values.label: Hospital shared room
values.comment: A room in a hospital for shared accommodation of patients.

values.label: Hospital private room
values.comment: A room in a hospital for private accommodation of a patient.

values.label: Bidding area
values.comment: An area for which bids can be made with the same price applicable to the whole area.

values.label: Price area
values.comment: An area for which the same price is applicable to the whole area.

values.label: Country of destination of equipment
values.comment: Country of the last place where the equipment will stop.

values.label: Aircraft airport stand
values.comment: Code used to specify the airport stand allocated to the aircraft.

values.label: Airport passenger terminal
values.comment: Code used to specify the airport terminal used for the embarking or disembarking of passengers.

values.label: Previous berth
values.comment: Place or location in a port where a vessel was previously moored.

values.label: Next berth
values.comment: Place or location in a port where a vessel will be moored, after moving from the current location.

values.label: Entity location
values.comment: Identifies the place or location of the entity.

values.label: Goods depot
values.comment: Depot where goods are received and are available for pick-up.

values.label: Disinfecting place
values.comment: Place where disinfection has been or must be performed.

values.label: Harbour rail station
values.comment: Rail station servicing a harbour.

values.label: Place of live animal care
values.comment: Place where live animal care has been or must be provided.

values.label: Phytosanitary control place
values.comment: Place where phytosanitary control has been or must be performed.

values.label: Place for re-icing or de-icing
values.comment: Place where re-icing or de-icing has been or must be performed.

values.label: Place of refuelling
values.comment: Place where refuelling has been or must be performed.

values.label: Place of provision of an unexpected service
values.comment: Place where an unexpected service has been or must be provided.

values.label: Private container terminal
values.comment: Container terminal managed or owned by a private company.

values.label: Railway container terminal
values.comment: Container terminal managed or owned by a railway company.

values.label: Inspection site
values.comment: The site where an inspection takes or took place.

values.label: Request only stop
values.comment: A location where a stop is only made on request.

values.label: Grid area
values.comment: A section of a grid.

values.label: Source power area
values.comment: The area that is the source of power.

values.label: Sink power area
values.comment: The area that is the destination of power.

values.label: Scheduled berth
values.comment: Place or location in a port where a vessel is scheduled to be moored.

values.label: Scheduled berth, bow
values.comment: Place or location in a port where the bow of a vessel is scheduled to berth.

values.label: Scheduled berth, stern
values.comment: Place or location in a port where the stern of a vessel is scheduled to berth.

values.label: Balance settlement area
values.comment: An area where common rules for balance settlement applies.

values.label: Market area
values.comment: An  area with common trading rules.

values.label: Metering grid area
values.comment: A physical area where consumption, production and exchange can be metered.

values.label: Climate zone
values.comment: A geographical area where the climate has common characteristics.

values.label: Country of birth
values.comment: Country where a person or an animal was born.

values.label: Country of fattening
values.comment: Country where an animal has been fattened.

values.label: Country of slaughter
values.comment: Country where an animal has been slaughtered.

values.label: Country of meat cutting
values.comment: Country where the meat is cut into pieces.

values.label: Meat cutting location
values.comment: A location where the meat is cut into pieces.

values.label: Slaughterhouse
values.comment: Place for the slaughter of animals as food.

values.label: Country of meat mincing
values.comment: Country where meat has been cut into very small pieces using a meat grinder.

values.label: Place of discharge and loading
values.comment: Place at which a means of transport is performing both discharge and loading operations, e.g. seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station.

values.label: Cargo facility location
values.comment: Name of the terminal, warehouse or yard where the goods are to be on or offloaded.

values.label: Tourist point of interest
values.comment: Code to specify that the location is a tourist point of interest.

values.label: Customs office of payment
values.comment: Place where Customs duties/taxes/fees have to be paid.

values.label: Conveyance facility location at departure
values.comment: Name of the location of the last facility (e.g. terminal, warehouse or yard) from which the conveyance will depart.

values.label: Conveyance facility location at arrival
values.comment: Name of the location of the initial facility (e.g. terminal, warehouse or yard) where the conveyance will arrive.

values.label: Bus station
values.comment: Name or identification of a bus station.

values.label: Ferry terminal
values.comment: Name or identification of a ferry terminal.

values.label: Place of packing
values.comment: Place where goods are packaged.

values.label: Country of assembly
values.comment: Country where product is assembled.

values.label: Town sales office
values.comment: The location is a town sales office.

values.label: Travel agency
values.comment: The location is a travel agency.

values.label: Inland clearance depot
values.comment: Depot where goods are cleared by the customs authorities or other governmental authorities in the interior of a country.

values.label: Place of final production
values.comment: Place where the production of the item was finalised.

values.label: Place of growth
values.comment: Place where the product was grown.

values.label: Place of intermediate production
values.comment: Place of any processing prior to final production.

values.label: Place of nutrient origin
values.comment: Place where the nutrient, or item of nourishing food, originated.

values.label: Place of package material production
values.comment: Place where the material used for packaging was produced.

values.label: Place of processing
values.comment: The place where the commodity was processed.

values.label: Place of species origin
values.comment: The place where the species was taken from the wild, or the place where the species was born, artificially propagated, grown or harvested.

values.label: Place of catch
values.comment: Place where the animal was caught, e.g. area of the ocean where the fish was harvested.

values.label: Government appeal office
values.comment: The location of a government office at which an appeal can be lodged.

values.label: Regulatory office of cross-border goods entry
values.comment: To identify the regulatory office at which the goods enter or are intended to enter the customs territory of destination.

values.label: Regulatory office of cross-border goods exit
values.comment: To identify the regulatory office at which the goods leave or are intended to leave the customs territory of dispatch.

values.label: Government approved establishment
values.comment: Facility approved for a specific purpose by a government authority.

values.label: Free trade zone
values.comment: A special area of a country where some normal trade barriers (e.g. tariffs and quotas) are eliminated, a.k.a. foreign free zone.

values.label: Place of physical examination
values.comment: A place where goods are to be examined.

values.label: Permitted location
values.comment: The location at which goods identified on the license, permit, certificate or other document are allowed to be moved or otherwise handled.

values.label: Landing location
values.comment: The place where a means of transport may be parked or tied up, e.g. wharf, quay, railyard, parking lot.

values.label: Place of loading on final means of transport
values.comment: Place where a consignment is placed aboard the means of transport which enters the destination customs territory.

values.label: Place of regulatory declaration review
values.comment: Location where the declaration is reviewed by appropriate government agency.

values.label: Travel document issuing country or political entity
values.comment: The country or political entity issuing the travel document.

values.label: Compliant facility, registered
values.comment: A facility that has been formally documented as compliant with regulations or statutes by a regulatory authority.

values.label: Bonded warehouse
values.comment: A building or other secured area in which dutiable goods may be stored, manipulated, or undergo manufacturing operations without payment of duty.

values.label: Goods destruction site, designated
values.comment: A place designated for the destruction of goods.

values.label: Goods disposal location, designated
values.comment: A place designated for the disposal of goods.

values.label: Incineration facility
values.comment: Facility with a furnace or apparatus for consuming materials completely or reducing materials to ash by burning.

values.label: Laboratory
values.comment: A facility equipped for scientific experimentation, research, testing or determination.

values.label: Place of assembly
values.comment: Facility where product is assembled.

values.label: Processing site
values.comment: Place where an operation or a series of operations are performed in the making or treatment of a product.

values.label: Quarantine facility
values.comment: A place or station where isolation is carried out.

values.label: Reclamation facility
values.comment: A facility where desired substances are recovered from materials or goods.

values.label: Refinery
values.comment: An industrial plant for refining a substance, such as petroleum or sugar.

values.label: Smelter
values.comment: A facility where ores are fused or melted in order to separate the metal contained in them.

values.label: Prescribed treatment facility
values.comment: A facility where goods are subjected to a prescribed treatment.

values.label: Embassy
values.comment: The official headquarters of an ambassador or official diplomat sent by one sovereign or state to another as its resident representative.

values.label: Region of source
values.comment: Region where goods were originally produced.

values.label: Region of storage
values.comment: Region where products have been stored.

values.label: Ship security incident location
values.comment: Location for reporting any security related matter to indicate where the safety/security incident has taken place.

values.label: Ship-to-ship activity location
values.comment: Location where the ship-to-ship activity has taken place.

values.label: Country of last processing
values.comment: The country where the trade item was last processed.

values.label: Fishing vessel
values.comment: Fishing vessel as a place of production.

values.label: Location of status
values.comment: The identification of the location of a status.

values.label: Location of meter
values.comment: The identification of the location of a meter.

values.label: Country of provenance
values.comment: The country of provenance of a consignment or product.

values.label: Meat mincing plant
values.comment: A place where the meat is cut into very small pieces using a meat grinder.

values.label: Place of fattening
values.comment: Place where an animal has been fattened.

values.label: Animal birth place
values.comment: Location where an animal was born.

values.label: Global Good Agricultural Practice Number (GGN)
values.comment: The Global Good Agricultural Practice Number (GGN) is a 13-digit number that uniquely identifies each producer and individual member of a producer group in the GLOBALG.A.P. Database.

values.label: Port of last waste delivery
values.comment: The name and country of the last port where waste of any type was delivered.

values.label: Port of next waste delivery
values.comment: The name and country of the next port where waste of any type will be delivered.

values.label: Effluent Treatment Plant
values.comment: A facility that cleans industrial and/or domestic effluents, before reusing the water or discharging it to the environment.

values.label: Farm
values.comment: An area of land, water or a building that is primarily devoted to agricultural or aquacultural processes, such as growing crops and/or keeping animals.

values.label: Manufacturing facility
values.comment: A facility where an operation or a series of operations are performed in the making or treatment of a product.

values.label: Animal Farm
values.comment: An area of land, water or a building that is primarily devoted to animals for the purpose of obtaining their meat, wool, hides, milk, eggs, etc.

values.label: Tannery
values.comment: A facility where the animal hides and/or skins are processed with tanning agents.

values.label: Textile mill
values.comment: Afacility wheretextiles, or types ofcloth, are produced or processed into finished products, such as clothing.

values.label: Textile dyeing mill
values.comment: A facility where textile products like fibres, yarns, and fabrics are dyed.

values.label: Forest Management Unit
values.comment: An identified area of land covered predominantly by forests, managed to a set of explicit objectives and according to a long-term forest management plan.

values.label: Mutually defined
values.comment: Place or location as agreed between the relevant parties.
